<h2>Eating</h2>

<p>We source the majority of our produce and food locally: our fresh fish comes from the local fishermen, milk and cheese comes from our neighbor&rsquo;s farm, in-season fruits are often purchased from local families, and our vegetables come from Chinandega&rsquo;s open-air municipal market.</p>

<figure class="figure figure--270x360 figure--pull-right">
  <div class="figure__media">
    <img alt="" height="360" src="assets/images/photo-accom-food.jpg" width="270">
  </div>
  <figcaption>A fresh Rancho Esperanza breakfast.</figcaption>
</figure>

<p>We serve three meals a day for our guests and volunteers, specializing in vegetarian, Asian, and Nicaraguan cuisine.</p>

<p>We begin serving breakfast at 7:30am and it is served ALL DAY! Choices include a large fruit plate, bagels, waffles, oatmeal, yogurt and granola, and eggs. Bottomless mugs of tea and great ecological coffee are served for $.75 until 10:30am.</p>

<p>Lunches and dinners are served family style at our large dining table with a vegetarian option always available. Dinner is the main meal of the day here and we keep it healthy and hearty with lots of vegetables and homemade sauces.</p>

<p>We offer a snack menu and local venders pass through selling fresh mangos, coconut bread, pasteles (little pastries), and, if we&rsquo;re lucky, the occasional ice cream.</p>

